
Overview of adj lurid

The adj lurid has 4 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (3) lurid -- (horrible in fierceness or savagery; "lurid crimes"; "a lurid life")
2. (3) lurid, shocking -- (glaringly vivid and graphic; marked by sensationalism; "lurid details of the accident")
3. (2) lurid -- (shining with an unnatural red glow as of fire seen through smoke; "a lurid sunset"; "lurid flames")
4. lurid -- (ghastly pale; "moonlight gave the statue a lurid luminence")
